// Accept fixture: a break-less `loop {}` in a match arm must not force the
// whole `match` expression to `Unit` when the other arm yields a value.
//
// A break-less loop has type `Never`; the match expression's type is the
// non-`Never` arm's type.  Before this fix, the loop was typed `Unit`,
// the match result was forced to `Unit`, and the `let y: i64` annotation
// caused a type mismatch.  The loop is wrapped in a block `{ loop {} }` —
// `loop` is a statement form in Hew and cannot appear as a bare match arm.
//
// Expected exit status: 3 (the `Some(3)` arm value), proving the match
// resolved to the payload of the non-loop arm.
fn main() -> i64 {
    let opt: Option<i64> = Some(3);
    let y: i64 = match opt {
        Some(n) => n,
        None => { loop {} },
    };
    y
}
